# @irys/arweave: Arweave Data Upload Package

## Installation

Install via npm or yarn:
```bash
npm install @irys/arweave
# or
yarn add @irys/arweave
```

## What It Does

This TypeScript/JavaScript SDK lets you interact with Arweave and upload data to the permaweb. It works in browsers and Node.js, offering "better typing, improved NodeJS compatibility" compared to the original arweave-js library.

## Basic API Usage

### Initialize Connection
```javascript
import Arweave from "@irys/arweave";
const arweave = new Arweave({ url: "https://arweave.net" });
```

### Upload Text/JSON Data
```javascript
let key = await arweave.wallets.generate();
let transaction = await arweave.createTransaction({
  data: JSON.stringify({ message: "Hello Arweave" })
}, key);

transaction.addTag("Content-Type", "application/json");
await arweave.transactions.sign(transaction, key);
await arweave.transactions.post(transaction);
```

### Upload Files
Use chunk uploading for larger files:
```javascript
let uploader = await arweave.transactions.getUploader(transaction);
while (!uploader.isComplete) {
  await uploader.uploadChunk();
}
```

## Pricing & Free Tier

The documentation doesn't mention free upload limits. Costs depend on data size and network congestion—you pay in AR (Arweave's native token). For bulk uploads, the package recommends using ArBundles or Irys instead.

